{
  "text": "When reviewing the therapeutic strategies for PAP, it is important to note that the various forms of PAP may require different treatments, even though whole-lung lavage is the current therapeutic standard [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . GM-CSF inhalation therapy [CITATION_3] and rituximab [CITATION_4] may also be effective treatments for autoimmune PAP. Several reports have shown that alveolar lavage and serial measurements of serum GM-CSF autoantibodies may prove useful for monitoring disease activity and response to treatment [CITATION_5] .",
